Birthday Examples

R Pruim

July 11, 2014

The Birthdays data frame contains information on the number of births each day in each US state over a period of approximately 20 years.

require(mosaic)
require(mosaicData)
head(Birthdays)
##   state year month day       date wday births
## 1    AK 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed     14
## 2    AL 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed    174
## 3    AR 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed     78
## 4    AZ 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed     84
## 5    CA 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed    824
## 6    CO 1969     1   1 1969-01-01  Wed    100
Birthdays %>% filter(state=="MI") -> MIBirths
MIBirths %>% 
  ggplot() +
  geom_line(aes(x=date, y=births, color=wday))

There are some days with very few births. Let’s remove those and remake our plot.

MIBirths %>% filter(births > 100) %>%
  ggplot() +
  geom_line(aes(x=date, y=births, color=wday))

require(mosaic)
BirthdaysWithAnnualBirths <-  
  Birthdays %>% 
  group_by(state, year) %>% 
  mutate(annualBirths=sum(births))
